* Software engineers have talked about “gremlins in the code” for decades
* Psychologists use “inner critic,” “parts,” and “voices” (like Internal Family Systems)
* Writers and comedians constantly personify abstract forces
* Even ancient cultures described emotions and forces as spirits or beings

So the mechanism predates both of us by a long shot.

